This paper is primarily focused on the study of formal languages and automata, which falls under the category of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). The paper also discusses the state complexity of operations over languages, which involves the manipulation of data structures and algorithms, falling under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the combination of individual operations, which involves the study of computational complexity and circuit complexity, falling under the categories of Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper also discusses methods of estimation and approximation, which involves the study of information theory and coding theory, falling under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
